thread.title: NSW dominates state economies

title: NSW dominates state economies
text:
Mon, Oct 26, 2015, 5:06 PM NZDT - New Zealand Markets closed for Labor Day NSW dominates state economies AAP – 1 hour 4 minutes ago Recommend Print 
NSW has retained the title of the best economically-performing state, boosted by a booming housing market and population growth. 
NSW took out the title for a fifth consecutive quarter, according to CommSec's State of the States report. 
It's the best performer for population growth, retail trade and housing construction and housing finance, and second to Tasmania on unemployment. 
CommSec chief economist Craig James said the gap between NSW and the rest of the pack continues to widen. 
"NSW has solid momentum," he said. 
"Population is above long term averages and that is driving home purchase and construction and retail spending. 
"As a result, jobs are being created, keeping the jobless rate stable." 
The states and territories are ranked on eight key measures. 
Victoria came in second, while the Northern Territory and Western Australia came in third.
